    "Tony W. Cartledge": "Eli\u2019s Fall and Samuel\u2019s Call\n[v_1Sa_2_27] 1 Sam 2:27\u20134:1a\nv. 4]; 132:11; Acts 2:30). While one might credit later writers with embellishing the\nnarrative for literary effect, it is more likely that the ancients regarded any word of Yahweh\nas the equivalent of an oath. Humans swore by the deity, but Yahweh had no reason to call\n[v_Isa_45_23] on a higher power; he could swear by himself (Isa 45:23; Jer 49:13; 51:14), by his holiness\n[v_Psa_89_35] (Ps 89:35 [MT",
